## Page Structure

Every feature page must follow this pattern:

```html
<div class="feature-name">
  <!-- Breadcrumb -->
  <app-breadcrumb [items]="breadcrumbs" />
  
  <!-- Page Header with Actions -->
  <h1 class="page-header">
    Page Title
    <div class="page-header__actions">
      <button class="btn btn--accent" (click)="openDialog()">
        + Add Item
      </button>
    </div>
  </h1>
  
  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="content-sections">
    <!-- Cards, grids, etc. -->
  </div>
</div>
```

### Breadcrumbs
**Component**: [breadcrumb/](mdc:src/app/shared/breadcrumb/)

```typescript
protected readonly breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbItem[] = [
  { label: 'Home', path: '/' },
  { label: 'Current Page' }
];
```

### Page Header Styling
- **Font size**: 28px (24px mobile)
- **Font weight**: 300 (light)
- **Margin-bottom**: 25px (20px mobile)
- **Display**: Flex with space-between
- **Color**: #242a30

## Grid System

Use 15px gaps (Color Admin standard):
```scss
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  gap: 15px;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
}
```

## Responsive Rules

### Mobile (< 768px)
- Sidebar: `translateX(-100%)` to hide
- Topbar brand: Auto width
- Search bar: Hidden
- User name: Hidden
- Content margin-left: 0
- Page header: Stack vertically
- Action buttons: Full width

## Z-Index Layers
- **Topbar**: 1010
- **Sidebar**: 1020
- **Sidebar Mobile Backdrop**: 1021
- **Dialogs**: Default Syncfusion (higher)

## Container Usage

**DO NOT** use `.container` class in feature pages when using admin layout. The main-content already provides appropriate padding and max-width handling.

**Remove** container divs from pages - layout padding is handled by `.main-content`.
